Dependencies: pgrep
* cmus - music player
* mpsyt - youtube player
* cmus-remote - allows control of cmus instance over commands
* xdotool - allows manipulation of most linux windows managers (confirmed on KDE)
* xbindkeys - Allows binding keys, easy to standardize across systems

Just copy over (and modify if needed) the desired shortcuts, categorised in files.
Copy to your xbindkeys config file (ex. ~/.xbindkeysrc).

To install and configure xbindkeys and other dependencies, look online as it varies between distros.
